==General Information==
'''Title:''' ''Sicut lilium inter spinas'' (not to be confused with [[Sicut lilium inter spinas I (Giovanni Pierluigi da Palestrina)|''Sicut lilium inter spinas'']] of the Song of Song cycle)<br>
{{Composer|Giovanni Pierluigi da Palestrina}}
'''Source of text:''' Song of Songs 2:2

{{Voicing|5|SATTB}}
{{Genre|Sacred|Motets}}
{{Language|Latin}}
{{Instruments|A cappella}}
{{Pub|1|1569|in ''{{NoCo|Liber primus motettorum}}''|no=21}}
{{Descr|A motet in two parts:<br>
1. Sicut lilium inter spinas<br>
2. Quam pulchri sunt gressus tui<br>
Palestrina composed a [[Missa Sicut lilium inter spinas (Giovanni Pierluigi da Palestrina)|parody mass]] on the basis of this motet.<br>'''}}
{{#ExtWeb:}}
==Original text and translations==
{{LinkText|Sicut lilium inter spinas}}
{{Text|Latin|
Sicut lilium inter spinas, sic amica mea inter filias Adae.
Alleluja.

Quam pulchri sunt gressus tui, filia principis,
collum tuum sicut turris eburnea, oculi tui divini
et comae capitis tui sicut purpura regis.
Quam pulchra es et quam decora, carissima.
Alleluja.}}

