==General Information==
{{Title|''Pulchrae sunt genae tuae''}}
{{Composer|Giovanni Pierluigi da Palestrina}}
'''Source of lyrics:''' Song of Solomon 1:10–12

{{Voicing|5|SATTB}}
{{Genre|Sacred|Motets}}
{{Language|Latin}}
{{Instruments|A cappella}}
{{Pub|1|1584|in ''{{NoCo|Canticum Canticorum}}''|no=6}}
{{Descr|From Song of Songs / Songs of Solomon - Chapter 1 - Verses 10 through 12.<br> The use of ''musica ficta'' in this piece (just as in many of Palestrina's works, and unlike e.g. in Lasso's pieces) is far from straightforward. Among the recordings of this piece rather differing realisations of ''musica ficta'' can be found. This regards primarily - but is not confined to - the B flat/natural in the opening motif (genae tuae), the B flat/natural in the motif Collum tuum.}}
{{#ExtWeb:
*[http://www.fourmilab.ch/etexts/www/Bible/Song_of_Solomon.html Texts of all the "Songs of Solomon" in English].
*[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Song_of_Songs Wikipedia's article on the "Songs of Solomon"].}}
==Original text and translations==
{{top}}{{Text|Latin|
:Pulchrae sunt genae tuae sicut turturis,
:collum tuum sicut monilia.
:Murenulas aureas faciemus tibi
:vermiculatas argento.
:Dum esset rex in accubitu suo,
:nardus mea dedit odorem suavitatis.}}
{{mdl|3}}
{{Translation|English|
:Thy cheeks are beautiful as the turtledove's,
:thy neck as jewels.
:We will make thee chains of gold,
:inlaid with silver.
:While the king was at his repose,
:my spikenard sent forth the odour thereof.}}
{{mdl|3}}
{{Translation|Dutch|
:Prachtig zijn je wangen, als van een tortelduif.
:Je hals is als een parelsnoer.
:Laten wij voor jou kettingen maken van goud
:ingelegd met stukjes zilver.
''[Zij:]''
:Zolang de koning op zijn rustbed lag
:verspreidde mijn nardusolie zijn lieflijke geur.}}
{{Translator|Anton Hendriks, Ben Terstegge & Hanneke Pot}}
{{btm}}
